        <mxCell id="G86pkJ9Fl34YANioCHnN-9" parent="1" style="image;aspect=fixed;html=1;points=[];align=center;fontSize=12;image=img/lib/azure2/identity/Multi_Factor_Authentication.svg;" value="" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="68" width="68" x="230" y="960" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="G86pkJ9Fl34YANioCHnN-11" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Functional Requirements:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Authentication:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;1. User is able to Register/Login.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Authorization:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;After Successful Registration, Users are authorize to following things:&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;User is able to Create/Delete Posts.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Users are able to follow each other.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Users are able to like comment each other.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Users are able to view Feed.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="180" width="590" x="50" y="40" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="G86pkJ9Fl34YANioCHnN-12" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;Non Functional Requirements:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;1. Availability &amp;gt;&amp;gt;&amp;gt; Consistency&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;As there are 500M-700M DAU&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We need to keep our social media up with negligible downtime.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;We can afford delay in like/comment/post/delete/feed to maintain consistency. But since we have to keep our application smoother a much higher latency is also unavoidable.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;2. Latency/Throughput&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Services provided by the social media application have to generate response in 30-50 ms.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;As, Latency and throughput are inversely proportional, lower the latency more the throughput means more requests should be handle.&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;b&gt;3. Scalability:&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Server scaling should be done appropriately for any event like A country winning a world cup multiple users are active at that particular period of time. So managing servers or make their replications is essential using a proper sharding technique..&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="320" width="590" x="50" y="210" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="G86pkJ9Fl34YANioCHnN-13" parent="1" style="text;html=1;whiteSpace=wrap;strokeColor=none;fillColor=none;align=left;verticalAlign=middle;rounded=0;" value="API Endpoints:&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;REGISTER&lt;br&gt;POST/api/REGISTER/users/new_user&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;LOGIN&lt;br&gt;GET/api/REGISTER/users/{user_id}&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Create Post&lt;br&gt;GET/api/Posts/user/{user_id}/{post_id}&lt;br&gt;POST/api/Posts/Create_post/users/new_post&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Like/Comment&lt;br&gt;GET/api/Like_comment/user/{user_id}/{post_id}&lt;br&gt;POST/api/Like_comment/users/{user_id}/{post_id}&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Follow&lt;br&gt;GET/api/Following/user/{user_id}? user_id=follow&lt;br&gt;POST/api/Follow/users/{user_id}? user_id=follow&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;Feed&lt;br&gt;Get/api/feed/users/{user_id}? user_id=feed" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="380" width="580" x="50" y="520" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
